summary: I thought the idea of Felicia having a son, and trying to move on from her criminal life was an interesting angle. At least, one...
body:
I thought the idea of Felicia having a son, and trying to move on from her criminal life was an interesting angle. At least, one I haven’t seen done with Black Cat.

(The stupid part about it was Peter’s automatic assumption that the kid was his because they slept together.) 

Shame The Heist basically said “nah” and it was all a lie because I was loving The Long Kiss Goodnight vibes I was getting before then.

summary: Guys, I’m completely finished with SPIDER-MAN PS4 and the Heist DLC.
body:
Guys, I’m completely finished with SPIDER-MAN PS4 and the Heist DLC.

I need someone to talk to about this. Cause your girl has thoughts.

No spoilers, but I loved Black Cat. She was sexy and confident and strong. Her new costume is a major upgrade from the comics and I ship her so hard with peter.

I loved Peter Parker and this version of him. Spider-man has always been one of my favorites because of how relatable I’ve found him. But, this story does that ten fold! Guys, I’m 23, the same age as Pete. And the whole break up and get back together thing he had with MJ, not having enough money or time for the things he loves (like writing requests on Tumblr), and his general snark was amazing and just me!

The villains were awesome and all the Marvel universe add ons (like my favorite pupper: Lockjaw!) were so fun to find.

I really liked the PS4 exclusive suits and I’m glad they added the MCU suits to.

They updated characters I care about and the story is so fun and fresh (like the twists at the end?!) and god damn, I can’t say more without spoiling.

I loved this story so much I’m playing it again till the next episode of the DLC comes out.

Sorry for the rant, I needed to get it out there.

Message me if you wanna chat about spoilers? It’s been it for over a month but still don’t wanna be rude.
